[I] C library in support of computations in number theory

[T] FLINT is a C library for doing number theory. At its core, FLINT provides
[T] arithmetic in standard rings such as the integers, rationals, algebraic,
[T] real, complex and p-adic numbers, finite fields, and number fields.

[U] https://www.flintlib.org/

[A] Flint Authors
[M] René Rebe <rene@exactco.de>

